[2026-04-18T17:05:08.531Z] [INFO]         "text": "Now I need to think about the best approach. The main Dockerfile doesn't COPY the repo into the image, so we can't simply run a script from the codebase. But we can use a `COPY` directive to add just the script. Let me check if this is feasible:\n\nActually looking again, both Dockerfiles need this to happen BEFORE copying any code. The cleanest approach is to:\n\n1. Create a **self-contained** `.mjs` script that doesn't import external libs (to work without the rest of the repo)\n2. Use `COPY` to add this single script (with its copy of the required data) into the Dockerfile\n3. OR: keep the script in `scripts/` but ensure it works standalone, and also add it to `src/` exports \n\nWait — the maintainer said: *\"Can we just have mjs file, like in scripts for that, to make it readable, easy to maintain and test? And also deduplicated. Or even may be we can reuse logic from src folder for the same?\"*\n\nThe best approach: \n- Create `scripts/configure-claude-quiet-defaults.mjs` that imports from `src/claude-quiet-config.lib.mjs` and `src/useless-tools.lib.mjs` \n- For the Dockerfile: COPY these 3 files in before running the script\n- For coolify Dockerfile: it already does COPY . . but after the quiet-config setup. We need to add an earlier, minimal COPY of just the 3 files we need.\n\nLet me approach this via a clean design:"
