[2026-04-18T17:06:48.939Z] [INFO]         "text": "Hmm, the `useless-tools.lib.mjs` uses `use-m` which requires network access at import time. That's a problem for Docker build that may not have internet access.\n\nWait, during Docker build, the image definitely has network (npm install works). Also, the claude-quiet-config.lib.mjs uses `import fs from 'node:fs/promises'` directly (no use-m). Let me check where we already use this use-m pattern in Docker:\n\nActually, looking at the existing bake-in script in the Dockerfile, it doesn't import `useless-tools.lib.mjs` — it just hardcodes the blocked list. The rationale may be that the Dockerfile wants to be standalone without network dependencies for the script step.\n\nBut during Docker build, network IS available (apt-get install works). So use-m should also work. Let me verify by testing:"
