[2026-04-18T17:06:55.497Z] [INFO]         "content": "138\t# --- Disable noisy/unused Claude Code features and tools (issue #1627, issue #1642) ---\n139\t# Autonomous headless hive-mind runs never benefit from tools that wait for\n140\t# human interaction (AskUserQuestion, EnterPlanMode) or that register local\n141\t# session cron jobs (CronCreate/List/Delete) or create worktrees\n142\t# (EnterWorktree/ExitWorktree) or fire mobile notifications\n143\t# (PushNotification) or kick off remote agent triggers (RemoteTrigger)\n144\t# or create notebook cells (NotebookEdit) or monitor processes (Monitor) or\n145\t# self-schedule wakeups (ScheduleWakeup). Pre-seed the user-scope\n146\t# ~/.claude/settings.json disallowedTools list so that even interactive\n147\t# claude sessions in this image do not surface them.\n148\t# The three claude.ai OAuth connectors (Gmail/Google Drive/Google Calendar)\n149\t# cannot be removed via `claude mcp remove` because they are not registered\n150\t# under user/local/project scope; solve.mjs filters them at run time using\n151\t# --strict-mcp-config --mcp-config <temp-file>.\n152\t#\n153\t# The configuration is applied by scripts/configure-claude-quiet-defaults.mjs,\n154\t# which reuses the canonical required env/settings/attribution/permissions\n155\t# maps and the idempotent merge helpers from\n156\t# src/claude-quiet-config.lib.mjs and src/useless-tools.lib.mjs so the\n157\t# Dockerfile, solve command, and tests stay in lock-step.\n158\tCOPY --chown=sandbox:sandbox \\\n159\t    src/claude-quiet-config.lib.mjs \\\n160\t    src/useless-tools.lib.mjs \\\n161\t    /workspace/.hive-mind-bake/src/\n162\tCOPY --chown=sandbox:sandbox \\\n163\t    scripts/configure-claude-quiet-defaults.mjs \\\n164\t    /workspace/.hive-mind-bake/scripts/\n165\tRUN mkdir -p /workspace/.claude && \\\n166\t    node /workspace/.hive-mind-bake/scripts/configure-claude-quiet-defaults.mjs \\\n167\t        --settings-path /workspace/.claude/settings.json && \\"
[2026-04-18T17:06:55.497Z] [INFO]       }
