[2026-04-18T17:07:15.575Z] [INFO]         "text": "The `ENV` directives (lines 38-49) set all the env vars at Docker image level (matches `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_AUTO_MEMORY=1` format the test expects). So the test at line 82 is satisfied. \n\nFor line 88 (settings): the test checks for `autoMemoryEnabled: false` (with space, like JSON serialized), or other forms. With my change, those won't appear in the Dockerfile anymore. The tests will fail.\n\nI need to update the tests to either:\n1. Check that the Dockerfile runs the script (simpler, correct after dedup)\n2. Check the library file has the values\n\nThe right thing is to update the tests to verify the Dockerfile delegates to the script. Let me examine useless-tools.test.mjs assertions for the Dockerfile:\n\nLooking at `useless-tools.test.mjs` lines 279-292:\n```js\nassert.ok(content.includes('disallowedTools'), 'Dockerfile should configure disallowedTools');\nassert.ok(content.includes('AskUserQuestion'), 'Dockerfile disallowedTools should include AskUserQuestion');\n```\n\nThese won't match either. All these test assertions need to be updated to validate the new indirection pattern.\n\nLet me think about the best approach. The cleanest thing is:\n- Tests verify the Dockerfile invokes the script  \n- Tests verify the settings show up in the generated settings.json by actually invoking the script in a temp dir\n\nLet me update:\n1. Tests\n2. Also update the coolify Dockerfile"
